      • convert

        public String convert(org.semanticweb.owlapi.model.OWLClassExpression ce,
                      String rootVariable,
                      boolean countQuery)
        Converts an OWL class expression into a SPARQL query with rootVariable as projection variable. It's possible to return it as COUNT query if wanted.
        Parameters:
        ce - the OWL class expression to convert
        rootVariable - the name of the projection variable in the SPARQL query
        countQuery - whether to return a SELECT (COUNT(?var) as ?cnt) query
        Returns:
        the SPARQL query

      • asQuery

        public com.hp.hpl.jena.query.Query asQuery(String rootVariable,
                                           org.semanticweb.owlapi.model.OWLClassExpression ce,
                                           Set<? extends org.semanticweb.owlapi.model.OWLEntity> variableEntities)
        Converts an OWL class expression into a SPARQL query with rootVariable as projection variable. It's possible to declare a set of OWL entities which will be replaced by variables in the query, that are then additionally used as projection variables and grouping variables.
        Parameters:
        ce - the OWL class expression to convert
        rootVariable - the name of the projection variable in the SPARQL query
        variableEntities - a set of entities that are replaced by variables
        Returns:
        the SPARQL query

      • asQuery

        public com.hp.hpl.jena.query.Query asQuery(String rootVariable,
                                           org.semanticweb.owlapi.model.OWLClassExpression ce,
                                           Set<? extends org.semanticweb.owlapi.model.OWLEntity> variableEntities,
                                           boolean countQuery)
        Converts an OWL class expression into a SPARQL query with rootVariable as projection variable. It's possible to declare a set of OWL entities which will be replaced by variables in the query, that are then additionally used as projection variables and grouping variables. Moreover, it's possible to return a COUNT query if wanted.
        Parameters:
        ce - the OWL class expression to convert
        rootVariable - the name of the projection variable in the SPARQL query
        variableEntities - a set of entities that are replaced by variables
        countQuery - whether to return a SELECT (COUNT(?var) as ?cnt) query
        Returns:
        the SPARQL query

      • setUseReasoning

        public void setUseReasoning(boolean useReasoning)
        Since SPARQL 1.1 there is a mechanism called property paths (see W3C rec.), which allows to add some kind of light-weight inferencing to a SPARQL query. Currently, we do the following if enabled
        • ?s rdf:type :A . -> ?s rdf:type/(rdfs:subClassOf|owl:equivalentClass)* :A .
        Note, this feature only works on query engines that support SPARQL 1.1 .
        Parameters:
        useReasoning - use inferencing
